Hazardous  environment  protective  garments  having  a  fusion  bonded  optically
transparent facepiece with olefin terpolymer seams (#6,302,993)
http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO1&Sect2=HITOFF&d=PALL&p=1&u=%2Fnetahtml
%2FPTO%2Fsrchnum.htm&r=1&f=G&l=50&s1=6,302,993.PN.&OS=PN/6,302,993&RS=PN/6,302,993
October 2001
The  invention  provides  a  process,  and  product  thereof,  for  forming  a  chemically  resistant  fusion  bonded
between chemically dissimilar materials by use of an acid-based terpolymer for protective garments. The olefin
terpolymers are preferably copolymers of an olefin, an acid and an ester. The process involves placing the
olefin terpolymer film between two dissimilar films such as a facepiece and the fabric material of the garments
and applying heat and pressure. The resulting fusion bonded film composite is strong, flexible and upon the
application of sufficient stress exhibits total cohesive rupture failure.

Preparation of phosphorus pentafluoride (#6,322,764)
