November 2001
A process for the preparation of anhydrous high purity phosphorus pentafluoride in high yield. The process
uses an excess of hydrogen fluoride in a reaction with a phosphoric acid to form hexafluorophosphoric acid
followed by reaction with a sulfur based acid reactant in a reaction medium containing an excess of hydrogen
fluoride.

